ce:section.ce:para:
As shown in Scheme 1, the fluorescence C-CQDPEGBA nanosponges were fabricated by the interparticle crosslinking of the CQDs with polyethylene glycol bisacrylate (PEGBA) via facile Michael addition reaction. After the crosslinking the CQDs of about 2 nm with PEGBA (Fig. 1
                        a), near spherical nanoparticles were obtained with a mean particle size of 61.6 ± 3.1 nm (Fig. 1b) in the TEM analysis. In the DLS analysis (Fig. 2
                        ), the raw CQDs showed a narrow hydrodynamic diameter around 2.8 nm. The average hydrodynamic diameter (Dh) of the nanoparticles obtained from the Michael addition was 131.5 nm with a PDI of 0.25. And the characteristic absorbance of the COC stretching vibration in PEG at 1110 cm−1 appeared in the FT-IR spectrum of the product [16], further revealing the successful crosslinking of the CQDs with PEGBA.
